# No Normalization-First Debugging

- Do not assume UI/API issues are normalization or coercion problems by default.
- Do not start with `Number()`, `parseInt`, enum coercion, string cleanup, or "normalization helper" changes.
- First prove the value at each boundary with direct evidence (runtime object, API response payload, and binding path).
- Treat contracts and known field shapes as authoritative; compare and use values directly unless a proven mismatch exists.
- Only introduce normalization when there is explicit proof of a contract mismatch at one specific boundary.
